oai_dc:dc.dc:title: New waterway before seeding
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Ray Rains is shown in waterway which he has completed on the Bell farm. Dimensions of waterway are twenty feet wide and one foot deep. waterway will be seeded to fescue and ladino clover this month. Located seven miles southeast of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
